<!channel> cross post from #compass-ux but want to make sure the larger team sees as well - 

Hey folks - some follow up information:

1. *It’s confirmed that the recent ambient minute solution is a go for launch*
Mobile will set a timestamp when an activity is logged so that we can maintain chronological order for the icons. It will not be stored on the the backend, so if a user deletes their app or goes back like 60 days the icons will likely be in a different order.

2. *It’s confirmed that we can have the number animate up from the last number the user saw for launch*
So if I open the app and it says 10 active minutes, I put it away, go walk around, then open it I will see the number tick up from 10 to 15 (for example) as my pattern animates to show the new density.

Wahoo!

Yea the first one took quite a bit of back and forth and coming up with a creative solution so thanks to everyone who helped and pushed on that! Will be a much better launch user experience because of it.
